  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/853",
  "title": "Create an easy to use API entry to preselect values",
  "body": "Being able to specify default selected values can be very handy in all list-related stuff.\n\nCurrently you have to dig inside the helper config etc (seehttp://stackoverflow.com/questions/35437004/algolia-initial-search-parameters-instantsearch-js/35440096#35440096).\n\nToday (feb 16) we had 4-5 people asking for this feature and how to do it (even Algolia employees)\n\nTo solve this recurring issue, I propose something like this:\n\n``` js\nrefinementList({\n ...,\n preselectedValues: ['..'],\n cssClasses: {\n    preselectedValues: 'hide'\n  } \n})\n```\n\nWhat do you think?\n",
